From 804aba611643e2a260f7d7dad4357c3eee36c742 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: MedPath Dev <medpath-dev@bot.local>
Date: Sat, 27 Jun 2026 10:49:08 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] refactor(workflow): implement focused 4-screen LIS workflow
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Screen 1 - Patient Registration (clean, no test panel)
- Removed test search sidebar from registration form
- Added 2-step stepper: Demographics → Clinical Info
- Added workflow trail progress indicator
- Added success overlay with Patient ID + countdown auto-navigate
- Validate step fields progressively before advancing

Screen 2 - Test Order (new dedicated page /dashboard/test-order)
- Full-width layout: search catalogue left, order panel right
- Popular test quick-pick grid (CBC, LFT, KFT, HbA1c, VTD, TSH, LIP)
- Category filter pills + real-time search
- Animated selected test list with remove button
- Priority selector (Routine/Urgent/STAT) with STAT alert
- Guard: redirects to /registration if no patient in flow

Screen 3 - Billing (dedicated, no test search)
- Patient banner (read-only) + tests summary (read-only)
- Separate discount/coupon/referral/advance fields
- Payment mode selector (Cash/UPI/Card/Credit)
- Invoice panel with live totals, outstanding calculation
- Payment receipt overlay → proceed to Sample Collection
- Guard: redirects to test-order if no tests selected

Screen 4 - Sample Collection
- Current patient block at top (tubes auto-generated from test categories)
- Tube colour coding (Green=Haematology, Red=Biochemistry, Purple=Endo, Yellow=Urine)
- Mark as Collected button with timestamp
- General lab queue table preserved below

PatientFlowService (new shared state service)
- Single source of truth across all 4 screens
- Holds patient, selected tests, priority, billing data
- Provides calcAge, generateInvoiceId, popularTests helpers

Router + Sidebar
- Added /dashboard/test-order route
- Sidebar reorganised: Patient Workflow section groups
  Register → Test Order → Billing → Sample Collection
